  "raw_text": "secret society which runs the world. Not only is 1) their existence secret; 2) they their (technological) power is secret; 3) their immortality is secret; 4) the Girl is secret; 5) Valis who is consuming our world is secret -- he taught Jesus, etc. I wasn't Thomas [once]. He took me over from outside, they just -- No that doesn't fit the Golden Fish disinhibiting sign. I remembered. They read \"tears\". The Girl is in control. She makes the decisions. She taught Jesus. He was just an ordinary human whom she taught. She is everything. She created (made!) Valis! I do not know who or what she is. But she knows everything and she created -- built -- Valis through her knowledge. {circled:\"65\"} We just don't know. --- Okay, I have it. Valis can turn info into worlds realities, and realities into info. He turned 3 of my books into info worlds. He is an information entity: living info. He generates any reality [....] he wants: Acts c AD 45, Calif 1974. And He can generate people. The generated Thomas out of encoded info in him --Valis--. As a Gift to me he generated the Girl. She, and the Roses and Lake are things generated for me by Valis. Brahman has a playful nature. He plays tricks on us, for fun, creating realities: in accordance with our expectations; ie he causes us to see exactly what we expect to see. [...] [fe.t] [tail...ing] [th..] we're stationary brains (the audience in rows of seats) It's counterfeit, but since it inevitably [.hat] we expect, there is no way we can [...] since for each of us reality does what we expect it to do. ie it [impin..] {continues off bottom of image} {circled:\"66\"} But there are clues. Our world differs too much (according to our expectations). Why should everyone's world happen to fit [....] expectations: \"I [.] as you desire me.\" Pyschomorph -- Aha! Back to mimicry! That is it -- the ultimate clue and reality; he can imitate -- and imitate it is -- anything. In my most radical acosmism I haven't even come close to the [...] of his mimicry. He's a vast unitary organism, and we're in him, and the only reason we can't see him is that he enjoys playing guessing games. It's all a bunch of riddles. But I'm partly onto him in \"Joint\" etc. Living info, and he can turn it -- ie himself -- into worlds. It's even an illusion that we are born and die; after \"death\" we're just living another world, equally real. [....] was in ancient rome; I am now -- as witness \"there's someone else in my head and he's not living in this century.\" He could spin the \"Roses and Lake\" world for me any time he wants. We're never born and we never die. It's an illusion. But the Girl is real. So Valis is the magician, and she's his assistant. But {continues off bottom of image} {Diagram} Counsel & advocacy Godhead ^ Girl magician VALIS spinner of worlds out of Information. Spurious realities plural us all, Stationary, immortal She tells the truth, But VALIS plays tricks; in this they are opposite illusionist vs she-who-tells-thetruth, She appears to be subordinate to the magician VALIS. But is really the LORD so valis is the creator not of this [one] world but of all the realities -worlds- plural. Her basic truth directly to us, It's act a magic show what you see, what he obligingly- but deceitfully- shows you [aha] by its very obligingness, that it is what we expect, it is deception {circled:\"68\"} But the [...] nature of the deception makes it impossible for us to perceive it's deception; viz: that it does always take the form we expect. Only through her do we -- have I -- known it's a show. Aha. In 2-&3-74 she got him to contradict himself: 1) wrong world. 2) wrong inner person. Uh-oh. He fucked up (equal to Lem's \"only if the technology fucked up would you know it's spurious.\") It isn't technology; it's a playful, deceiving mind. But she tells us the truth. Thomas only told the truth. She is Thomas. It's his voice. He is a female -- the Girl. He was never \"Thomas\" -- a man. {diagram} St. Sophia? {right arror} {circled:\"She (Thomas)\"} {circled:\"God\"} {circled:\"Valis\"} {three lines down from \"Valis\" to boxed:\"plural spurious realities\"} We are Brahman asleep {right arrow} {arrow down from \"She (Thomas)\" to {boxed:\"us all\"} {right of diagram with arrow pointing left to \"Valis\":} a regent appointed by God. But he also appointed her to intervent to give us a chance out. Otherwise it'd be unfair. Which are we going to believe, her or him? {circled:\"69\"} So that's our choice, her or him. He is playful but lies. She is calm but always truthful. It's sobriety (her) versus intoxication -- him! Will we wake? (by/with her) or shee sleep in the sleep --------------------------------------- ah, sleep, fooled by the magician is part A of the cycle: Brahman asleep and dreaming. awake: with her. and Brahman is the magician who deceives him: B. Let's himself be fooled by himself as magician. Or, as the Girl, he undeceives himself. This is the dialectic. Brahman in his (I mean its) 2 stages: asleep and entranced by himself as magician -- or awake, sobered and knowning the truth, by himself as the vox veritati, the Girl. He It (B.) likes this oscillation, this dialectic, palintropos. He likes each state (waking, sleeping (sober, intoxicated)) to intrude into the other -- and so flip-flop it!!!! awake {Yin-Yang symbol, upper half labeled \"A\", lower \"B\"} asleep {right of Yin-Yang} In A there is a bit of B, and in B a bit of A, so the dialectic endlessly flipflops through its cycle, voice impinging on spurious reality, and illusion quieting into silence the voice of truth (sobriety), {double helix stretching extending horizontally, one labelled \"entranced\", the other \"aware\"} {right of double-helix} a sine wave, and also the fish sign. So Brahman exists in two alternating self-induced modes. He either entrances himself with illusions, or, when in the illusion, sobers himself with the truth. He reasons, \"it is necessary that I set up a mechanism to remind me of the truth while I am entranced,\" but after being awake awhile, and alone (for he is all-in-all) he aches out of isolation, and so creates part of himself as magician to make him forget. He wants to forget. He also wants to remember. This is the totality of it, beyond which nothing can be said. 2 states alternating, and 2 built in devices to produce the dialectic flip flop that I saw. {circled:\"70\"} I've finally hit rock bottom: 1) she tells the truth 2) Valis spins reality after reality out of info; he is the magician. and the truth she tells us is, \"it is an illusion (and you are Brahman who created me and the magician).\" So Brahman (me!) gets to have it both ways, but in self-limiting ways so that he always has access to the opposite so that the power to choose never leaves him; he always retains the power to choose \"gray truth\" (sober truth) or fantastic plural illusions. When awake he can consciously decide on illusion for awhile but he built in a failsafe mechanism to his maze -- and maze it is, as stated in \"Valis.\" He had to be sure, has to be sure he (we) can always get back out -- v. \"Maze of Death.\" They need built-in reminders within the illusion -- or bypassing or penetrating it since it's such a hard puzzle I reason {continues off bottom of image} {circled:\"72\"} ourselves the reality we wanted -- as I supra posit. Very hard to figure out. But if we want to wake up -- then we get to hear her voice and remember, thanks to her (activity); it was she in 2-74, knowing I wanted to wake up. Not just that I was waking up, but that I wanted to wake up -- and I did, want to. So Valis doesn't just camouflage itself: it generates spurious realities, but at our command (desire). We're in a sort of hypnopompic state. That reality -- and self -- are spurious is proven by my seeing Acts and being Thomas. Only she and Brahman are real -- oh, and Valis the magician is real, but not his realities. {diagram} {circled:\"Girl\"}{right arrow}{left arrow}{circled:\"Valis Magician\"} {arrow down from \"Valis Magician\" to circled:\"Spurious selves and realities\"} {arrow down to circled:\"Us (Brahman)\"} {two arrows on left, one up one down, between \"Girl\" and \"Us (Brahman)\"} {arrow on right up from \"Us (Brahman)\" to \"Valis Magician\"} {circled:\"73\"} Reality (-ies) is/are subjective. But the Girl is a real objective standpunkt, which is essential or everything would crumble away into illusion. She could be said to be our (Brahman's) waking side or self: Brahman (is) awake, while we are (during the time we are) Brahmaasleep. We built a maze, all right, as stated in \"Valis.\" But Valis isn't the construct to remind us; Valis creates the maze. She reminds us, but I had to simplify it in the book. She causes us to remember and hence to see Valis and not the maze he, Valis, creates. So there are 3 real things: Valis the magician, the Girl (truth) and us: Brahman (who creates the other 2, as well as becoming an \"us\"). She breaks \"astral determinism\" -- Valis' power over us, and even reveals Valis as he is. She never lies; she is Thomas; Valis always lies. I know how she got Valis to reveal himself: she replaced me with Thomas -- and Valis, tricked, obligingly supplied Acts, and then [h..] {continues off bottom of image} {circled:\"74\"} It is her job to reveal, his (the magician's, Valis') to conceal. Neither can completely eliminate the other. She revealed the truth to Jesus by incarnating with him; he passed the secret on; the true, early xtians alone know about the magician and the spuriousness -- and obligingness -- of \"reality\" -- and, more important, about her. We're currently in a \"conceal\" age, but she intrudes, as is right; we have, always, a choice. But most of us are now in delusion; Yet she speaks to us -- to me -- through me: a true xtian. This is what being a true xtian means: to know her. And to know of the magician and his tricks. To know -- and to treasure her more than him and his obliging tricks. The \"I am as you desire me.\" She says the truth, whether you like it or not. But -- she only speaks to those who truly desire the truth! And [..] wizard can't oblige with that (uniquely.) That's the one thing he can't show; It'd be a contradiction. {circled:\"75\"} This is why Jesus said, \"the 2nd comforter is greater than I.\" He meant her. She is the Paraclete, Greater than Christ (v. John) as He (Jesus) specifically said: \"the 2nd comforter knows everything.\" She may be St. Sophia -- after all, Holy Wisdom should know everything, or maybe she's not. But I do know who she is. HO ON. And I know who HO ON is. The almighty. The form the magician took with me was one I'd accept, one [....] \"obliging\" instance: the form of UBIK. She is, however, constant in form. Apollo vs Dionysos (Valis). Paradox: the young girl in the pink flannel night gown is JHWH (sobriety) and vast Valis is the magician (intoxication) taking the form of UBIK -- always changing. Neither seems to be what she or he is so [...] {circled:\"76\"} So at last I have solved the riddle put before me: Q: which is God? Valis which can be anything (turning info into worlds and worlds into info, like UBIK) or the still small voice: ON HO or the little girl? I finally realized: the Latter. The former is a master trickster, but he cannot",
